==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Monosulphide
<hw>Mon`o*sul"phide</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Mono-</ets> + <ets>sulphide</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A sulphide containing one atom of sulphur, and analogous to a
monoxide; -- contrasted with a <ant>polysulphide</ant>; <as>as, galena
is a <ex>monosulphide</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monosulphuret</ent>⟦br⟧
